&lt;p&gt;The Royal Cornwall Hospitals Trust is a developing Trust situated in the beautiful county of Cornwall serving a population of around 500,000 people.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen to appoint a Band 5 Scrub Practitioner at West Cornwall Hospital, Penzance.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;West Cornwall Hospital is a very busy Day Case unit comprising 2 theatres undertaking Gynaecology, Urology, Upper GI, Colorectal, Maxillo-Facial, Oral Surgery and Ophthalmology.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a vibrant, motivated, flexible and adaptable practitioner who is able to demonstrate excellent team working, communication and interpersonal skills. We are seeking a practitioner who is flexible and adaptable with excellent scrub and organisational skills and most importantly, unlimited enthusiasm&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a part time post working 28.5 hours per week&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Nicola Brown - Team Lead 01736 874157&lt;/p&gt;
